Access rights statementc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/AccessRightsStatement

A formal statement indicative of licensing terms for the use of a resource (e.g., open access, free to read , etc.); its semantics should be clear, preferrably formally expressed and documented at a URL
has super-classes
is in range of
access rights op
has members
copyright not evaluated ni, copyright undetermined ni, embargoed access ni, in copyright ni, in copyright e u orphan ni, in copyright edu ni, in copyright n c permitted ni, in copyright rights holders unlocatable ni, metadata only access ni, no copyright ni, no copyright contract ni, no copyright n c ni, no copyright u s ni, no known copyright ni, open access ni, open access1 ni, restricted access ni, restricted access1 ni

Access rights statement identifierc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/AccessRightsStatementIdentifier

A string used to uniquely identify an access rights statement according to a specific scheme
has super-classes
identifier c
has members
c 14cb ni, c 16ec ni, c abf2 ni, c f1cf ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/CNE/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/InC-EDU/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/InC-NC/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/InC-OW-EU/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/InC-RUU/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/InC/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/NKC/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/NoC-CR/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/NoC-NC/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/NoC-OKLR/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/NoC-US/1.0/ ni, http://rightsstatements.org/vocab/UND/1.0/ ni, omtd access1 ni, omtd access2 ni

Actorc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/Actor

A person, organization or group that participates in an event or process
has super-classes
agent c, type of described entity c
is in domain of
actor related to op, is IPR holder of op, is annotator of op, is contact for op, is distribution rights holder of op, is evaluator of op, is funder of op, is licensor of op, is recorder of op, is resource creator of op, is resource provider of op, is validator of op
is in range of
IPR holder op, annotator op, contact op, distribution rights holder op, evaluator op, funder op, is related to actor op, recorder op, resource creator op, resource provider op, validator op

Componentc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/Component

A piece of software typically intended for a specific technical purpose, such as a particular implementation of a part-of-speech tagger (e.g TreeTagger), a tree parsing program (e.g., mstparser), etc. It is wrapped in a standard way within a particular component-oriented framework such as UIMA, GATE, etc. or as a specific type of web service.
has super-classes
Language Technology tool/service c

Corpusc back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/Corpus

is in domain of
corpus subclass op, has aligned version op, has annotated version op, is aligned version of op, is annotated version of op, user query dp
is in range of
has aligned version op, has annotated version op, is aligned version of op, is annotated version of op

Data language resourcec back to ToC or Class ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/DataLanguageResource

A resource composed of linguistic material used to assist and augment language processing applications, but also, in a broader sense, in language and language-mediated research studies and applications; examples include data sets (textual, multimodal/multimedia and lexical data, grammars, language models, etc.) in machine readable form
has super-classes
Language Resource c
has sub-classes
Corpus c, Language description c, Lexical/Conceptual resource c
is in domain of
anonymization details dp, anonymized dp, has converted version op, is archived by op, is converted version of op, is queried by op, is related to LT tool/service op, personal data details dp, personal data included dp, sensitive data details dp, sensitive data included dp
is in range of
LT tool/service related to op, has archived op, has converted version op, is converted version of op, queries op

condition of useop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/conditionOfUse

Links a licence with a specific condition/term of use imposed for accessing a language resource. It is an optional element and only to be taken as providing brief human readable information on the fact that the language resource is provided under a specific set of conditions. These correspond to the most frequently used conditions imposed by the licensor (via the specified licence). The proper exposition of all conditions and possible exceptions is to be found inside the licence text. Depositors should, hence, carefully choose the values of this field to match the licence chosen and users should carefully read that licence before using the language resource.
has domain
Licence c
has range
Condition of use c

is licensor ofop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/isLicensorOr

Links to the resource(s) which a person or organisation is legally eligible to license and actually licenses. The licensor could be different from the creator, the distributor or the IPR holder. The licensor has the necessary rights or licences to license the work and is the party that actually licenses the resource that is distributed via the specific channel. She will have obtained the necessary rights or licences from the IPR holder and she may have a distribution agreement with a distributor that disseminates the work under a set of conditions defined in the specific licence and collects revenue on the licensor's behalf. The attribution of the creator, separately from the attribution of the licensor, may be part of the licence under which the resource is distributed (as e.g., is the case with Creative Commons Licences).
has super-properties
actor related to op
has domain
Actor c
has range
Distribution c
is inverse of
licensor op

licensorop back to ToC or Object Property ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/licensor

The person or organisation who is legally eligible to license and actually licenses the resource. The licensor could be different from the creator, the distributor or the IPR holder. The licensor has the necessary rights or licences to license the work and is the party that actually licenses the resource that is distributed via the specific channel. She will have obtained the necessary rights or licences from the IPR holder and she may have a distribution agreement with a distributor that disseminates the work under a set of conditions defined in the specific licence and collects revenue on the licensor's behalf. The attribution of the creator, separately from the attribution of the licensor, may be part of the licence under which the resource is distributed (as e.g., is the case with Creative Commons Licences).
has super-properties
is related to actor op
has domain
Distribution c
has range
Person c
is inverse of
is licensor of op

annotation schemeni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: http://w3id.org/meta-share/meta-share/annotationScheme

A set of elements and values designed to annotate data. It usually consists in a formal representation. It aims to represent a specific level of information, such as morphological features of words, syntactic dependency relations between phrases, discourse level information , etc. It can consist of a flat structure of elements and values (e.g., part-of-speech tags) or it can be more complex with interrelated elements (e.g., specific morphological features to be used for each part-of-speech).
belongs to
LCR subclass c
